       Creates path categories using conditions for grouping  paths  according
       to  analyzed  timing  results.  The command can be applied wherever the
       user loads the machine readable timing report. For more information  on
       creating  path categories, see "Creating Path Categories" in the Debug-
       ging Timing Results chapter of User Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each create_path_category parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_path_category

       -clock {both | launch | capture}
              Helps you search the Clock Tree instead of  the  data  path.  If
              this option is not specified, the user searches the data path by
              default. You can use one of the following values:

              * Both: searches on launch or capture clock paths.

              * Launch: searches only on launch clock paths

              * Capture: searches only on capture clock paths

              Note: Supports simultaneous criteria on data path.

       -comment {<commentText>}
              Specifies a comment that is associated with the category.

       -master <existing_category_name>
              Specifies  that  the  new category should be created as a nested
              category of the specified master category. The  master  category
              should be an existing category.

              Default:  If  you do not specify this parameter, the category is
              created as a new category at the top level.

       -name <group_name>
              Specifies the name of the category to be created.

       -overwrite
              Overwrites any predefined category with the same  name  in  your
              category list.

       -sdc {<file_name> <line_number>}
              Creates a category based on the SDC constraint as per the speci-
              fied  SDC  file  name  and line number. Creating a path category
              based on an SDC constraint helps you to analyze the affect of an
              SDC constraint by grouping the affected paths together.

       -check_type {Setup Check | Hold Check

              | Clock Gating Setup Check

              | Library Clock Gating Setup Check

              | Clock Gating Hold Check

              | Library Clock Gating Hold Check

              | External Delay Assertion

              | Latch Borrowed Time Check

              | PulseWidth Check | ClockPeriod Check

              | Recovery Check | Removal Check}" Indicates that the check type
              matches the specified option.

              Type: String, optional

              Note: Use quotes ("") or curly braces ({}) to specify the  value
              of this option.

       -critical_false_path <string>
              Specifies the critical false path.

              Type: String, optional

       -file <string>
              Specifies the file name.

              Type: String, optional

       -from_inst | -from_inst_pointer | -from_pin | -from_cell | -from_clock
       | -from_port | -from_port_pointer | -from_pd <string>
              Indicates  that  the  path  must be from the specified instance,
              pin, cell, clock, power domain, or port pattern.

       -from_clock_edge <string>
              Indicates that the path must be from the specified clock edge.

              Type: String, optional

       -incr_delay_of_any_net <float>
              Indicates that the incremental delay of  at  least  a  net  that
              matches the specified float value.

       -incr_delay_of_every_net <float>
              Indicates  that  the incremental delay of every net that matches
              the specified float value.

              Type: String, optional

       -not_from_inst | -not_from_pin

              | -not_from_cell | -not_from_clock

              | -not_from_port | -not_from_pdstring" Indicates that  the  path
              must  not  be  from the specified instance, pin, cell, clock, or
              port pattern.

       -through_inst | -through_pin

              | -through_cell | -through_net

              | -through_port | -through_pd<string>" Indicates that  the  path
              must  be  through  the specified instance, pin, cell, net, power
              domain, or port pattern.

       -not_from_clock_edge
              Indicates that the path must not be  from  the  specified  clock
              edge.

              Type: String, optional

       -not_through_inst | -not_through_pin

              | -not_through_cell | -not_through_net

              |  -not_through_port  | -not_through_pd <string>" Indicates that
              the path must not be through the specified instance, pin,  power
              domain, cell, net, or port pattern.

       -not_to_clock_edge
              Indicates that the path must not be to the specified clock edge.

              Type: String, optional

       -to_inst | -to_inst_pointer | -to_pin | -to_cell | -to_clock | -to_port
       | -to_port_pointer | -to_pd <string>
              Indicates  that  the  path  must be the specified instance, pin,
              cell, clock, power domain, or port pattern.

       -not_to_inst | -not_to_pin

              | -not_to_cell | -not_to_clock

              | -not_to_port | -not_to_pd <string>" Indicates  that  the  path
              must  not  be to the specified instance, pin, cell, clock, power
              domain, or port pattern.

       -slack <float>
              Indicates that the slack of the path must  match  the  specified
              <float> value.

       -skew <float>
              Indicates  that  the  skew  of the path must match the specified
              <float> value.

       -launch_latency <float>
              Indicates that the launch latency of the  path  must  match  the
              specified <float> value.

       -capture_latency <float>
              Indicates  that  the  capture latency of the path must match the
              specified <float> value.

       -uncertainty <float>
              Indicates that the uncertainty of the path must match the speci-
              fied <float> value.

       -number_of_insts <integer>
              Indicates that the number of instances in the data segment (with
              launch and capture clock paths) must match the specified  <inte-
              ger> value.

       -number_of_insts_of_name <string_plus_integer>
              Indicates  that  the  number of instances matching the specified
              instance name match the specified <integer> value.

       -number_of_insts_not_of_name <string_plus_integer>
              Indicates that the number of instances not matching  the  speci-
              fied instance name match the specified <integer> value.

       -number_of_insts_of_celltype <string_plus_integer>
              Indicates  that  the  number of instances matching the specified
              celltype match the specified <integer> value.

       -number_of_insts_not_of_celltype <string_plus_integer>
              Indicates that the number of instances not matching  the  speci-
              fied celltype match the specified <integer> value.

       -to_clock_edge
              Type: String, optional

       -total_delay_of_insts <float>
              Indicates  that  the total delay of instances matches the speci-
              fied <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_level_of_chain_of_insttype
              Type: String, optional

       -total_delay_of_path <float>
              Indicates that the total delay of  path  matches  the  specified
              <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_nets <float>
              Indicates  that  the  total  delay of nets matches the specified
              <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_insts_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the total delay of instances matching the  speci-
              fied name matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_insts_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the  total  delay of instances not matching the
              specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_insts_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the total delay of instances matching the  speci-
              fied celltype matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_insts_not_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the  total  delay of instances not matching the
              specified celltype matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_nets_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the total delay of nets  matching  the  specified
              name matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_delay_of_nets_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the total delay of nets not matching the speci-
              fied name matches the specified <float> value.

       -total_incr_delay_of_path <float>
              Indicates that the total incremental delay of path  matches  the
              specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_inst <float>
              Indicates  that  the delay of any instance in the design matches
              the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_net <float>
              Indicates that the delay of any net in the  design  matches  the
              specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_inst <float>
              Indicates that the delay of every instance in the design matches
              the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_net <float>
              Indicates that the delay of every instance in the design matches
              the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_inst_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that the delay of any instance in the design matching
              the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_inst_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of  any  instance  in  the  design  not
              matching the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_inst_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that the delay of any instance in the design matching
              the specified celltype matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_inst_not_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of  any  instance  in  the  design  not
              matching  the  specified  celltype matches the specified <float>
              value.

       -delay_of_any_net_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of any net in the design  matching  the
              specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_any_net_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the delay of any net in the design not matching
              the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_inst_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of every instance in the design  match-
              ing the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_inst_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the  delay  of every instance in the design not
              matching the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_inst_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of every instance in the design  match-
              ing the specified celltype matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_inst_not_of_celltype <string_plus_float>
              Indicates  that  the  delay  of every instance in the design not
              matching the specified celltype matches  the  specified  <float>
              value.

       -delay_of_every_net_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of every net in the design matching the
              specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -delay_of_every_net_not_of_name <string_plus_float>
              Indicates that the delay of every net in the design not matching
              the specified name matches the specified <float> value.

       -view  Type: String, optional

Examples:
              * The  following command categorizes paths whose source clock is
                vclk1:

                create_path_category -name vclk1 -from_clock vclk1

                The category vclk1 is created.

              * The following command categorizes paths whose skew  is  larger
                than 0.2:

                create_path_category -name worst_skew -skew {> 0.2}

                The category worst_skew is created.

              * The following command creates paths from the macros in the de-
                sign:

                create_path_category    -name    from_RAM_128x16    -from_inst
                RAM_128x16

              * The following command creates paths to the macros in  the  de-
                sign:

                create_path_category -name to_RAM_128x16 -to_inst RAM_128x16

              * The  following command creates paths between the macros in the
                design:

                create_path_category  -name   between_RAM_128_256   -from_inst
                RAM_128x16 -to_inst RAM_256x16

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

